{
  "texts": [
    "The conceptual roots of this perspective can be traced back to [54].",
    "These systems represent a structural and functional evolution from conventional E2E models, shifting the focus from acoustic-driven generation to language-model-driven in-Unified Embedding Space Text Encoder Fused Features Text Input Text Decoder Text Output Audio Encoder Text Embedding Space Audio Embedding Space Audio Embedding Text Embedding Audio Input Modality Feature Extraction Modality Information Fusion LLM Inference Adaptor Fig. 4: Overview of Speech LLM Architectures with Speech and Text Inputs and Text Outputs.terpretation.",
    "Unlike traditional AED-based architectures, LLM-Centric systems align speech inputs to the text modality and utilize LLMs for decoding, generation, and reasoning [26], [27], [30], [31].",
    "This cross-modal design not only enables transfer to diverse downstream tasks-such as summarization, translation, and question answering-but also brings enhanced modularity, interpretability, and instruction-following capability [28], [29], [32], [33].Recent advances in LLM-Centric architectures have enabled unprecedented levels of task generalization and language comprehension in speech understanding.",
    "It is important to distinguish true LLM-Centric approaches from conventional cascaded systems that merely connect ASR outputs to an LLM."
  ]
}